<Docs title="Remote & Split Mode">
  <h2>Remote Capture</h2>
  <p>
    Use <code>rdc remote</code> to capture from a remote RenderDoc target and
    pull the <code>.rdc</code> file back locally.
  </p>
  <pre><code>rdc remote connect 10.0.0.219:39920
rdc remote list
rdc remote capture /usr/bin/vkcube -o /tmp/remote.rdc</code></pre>

  <h2>Split Mode</h2>
  <p>
    Split mode lets a thin client (for example macOS) connect to a daemon that
    has RenderDoc installed.
  </p>
  <pre><code># replay host (Linux/Windows)
rdc capture --output /tmp/game.rdc -- /path/to/game
rdc open /tmp/game_frame0.rdc --listen 0.0.0.0:54321

# thin client (macOS)
PYTHONPATH=src .venv/bin/rdc open --connect host:54321 --token TOKEN
PYTHONPATH=src .venv/bin/rdc capture --output /tmp/mac_capture.rdc -- /usr/bin/vkcube
PYTHONPATH=src .venv/bin/rdc close --shutdown</code></pre>

  <h2>Notes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>In split mode, capture and remote commands are routed through daemon RPC.</li>
    <li>The resulting <code>.rdc</code> file is downloaded back to the client output path.</li>
    <li>No local RenderDoc installation is required on split clients.</li>
  </ul>
</Docs>
